### How to add the lists to your ZeroNet? ###

[code]
=== For this example; lets ad the below to our list. ===

    "11SDMs9ry1uekwdupLrWdAag9HY5dPktE": {
      "cert_user_id": "11SDMs9ry1uekwd@08chan",
      "date_added": 1566262118.1790304,
      "reason": "L0:Pedo",
      "source": "1DdPHedr5Tz55EtQWxqvsbEXPdc4uCVi9D"
    },
[/code]
>Go into your ZeroNet\data directory and you will find a .JOSN file called filters. open it.

### THIS PART IS FOR IF YOUR LIST IS BLANK!! ###

>if you are new to ZN it will look like this.
[code]
{
  "includes": {},
  "mutes": {}
  },
  "siteblocks": {}
}
[/code]
>Paste the list into  "mutes": {} within the curly braces as shown below and...
>this is important, don't fuck this up... REMOVE THE COMMA "," FROM THE LAST ITEM!
[code]
  "mutes": {
    "11SDMs9ry1uekwdupLrWdAag9HY5dPktE": {
      "cert_user_id": "11SDMs9ry1uekwd@08chan",
      "date_added": 1566262118.1790304,
      "reason": "L0:Pedo",
      "source": "1DdPHedr5Tz55EtQWxqvsbEXPdc4uCVi9D"
    } <<(NOTE HOW I HAVE REMOVED THE ",")
  },
[/code]
IMPORTANT! Again note the syntax! The last entry in an object does not have a "," at the end of the "}". this is part of the JOSN syntax, make sure you keep the syntax!
you should now go to the bottom of this post where is says "Check your list is working and valid."


### THIS PART IS FOR IF YOU ALREADY HAVE ENTRY'S IN YOUR LIST!!! ###


>If you already have items in the list, It will look like this
[code]
{
  "includes": {},
  "mutes": {
    "12s9iKaT8AH1dSjRozaRhsTTqgVdP7govo": {
      "cert_user_id": "hypnothize@zeroid.bit",
      "date_added": 1566260631.2308621,
      "reason": "Bad User",
      "source": "1DdPHedr5Tz55EtQWxqvsbEXPdc4uCVi9D"
    }
  },
  "siteblocks": {}
}
[/code]
>Paste the items into "mutes": {" at the top of the list as shown below.
E:G:
[code]
  "mutes": {
    "11SDMs9ry1uekwdupLrWdAag9HY5dPktE": {
      "cert_user_id": "11SDMs9ry1uekwd@08chan",
      "date_added": 1566262118.1790304,
      "reason": "L0:Pedo",
      "source": "1DdPHedr5Tz55EtQWxqvsbEXPdc4uCVi9D"
    },
    "12s9iKaT8AH1dSjRozaRhsTTqgVdP7govo": {
      "cert_user_id": "hypnothize@zeroid.bit",
      "date_added": 1566260631.2308621,
      "reason": "Bad User",
      "source": "1DdPHedr5Tz55EtQWxqvsbEXPdc4uCVi9D"
    }
  },
[/code]
You are now done.

### Check your list is working and valid. ###

There is a simple way to check that you have not fucked up your filters file.

>go to ZeroNet home
>Click the three dots in the top left.
>Click "Manage blocked users and sites."
It now should be populated with 08chan entry's, with the list category and reason. If it is blank, you likely fucked up and have a missing/have an extra "," or "}" somewhere.

